15namespace cricket {

17using webrtc::RTCError;
18using webrtc::RTCErrorType;
19
20RTCError VerifyCandidate(const Candidate& cand) {
21 // No address zero.
22 if (cand.address().IsNil() || cand.address().IsAnyIP()) {
23 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
24 "candidate has address of zero");
25 }
26
27 // Disallow all ports below 1024, except for 80 and 443 on public addresses.
28 int port = cand.address().port();
29 if (cand.protocol() == cricket::TCP_PROTOCOL_NAME &&
30 (cand.tcptype() == cricket::TCPTYPE_ACTIVE_STR || port == 0)) {
31 // Expected for active-only candidates per
32 // http://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc6544#section-4.5 so no error.
33 // Libjingle clients emit port 0, in "active" mode.
34 return RTCError::OK();
35 }
36 if (port < 1024) {
37 if ((port != 80) && (port != 443)) {
38 return RTCError(RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
39 "candidate has port below 1024, but not 80 or 443");
40 }
41
42 if (cand.address().IsPrivateIP()) {
43 return RTCError(
44 RTCErrorType::INVALID_PARAMETER,
45 "candidate has port of 80 or 443 with private IP address");
46 }
47 }
48
49 return RTCError::OK();
50}
51
52RTCError VerifyCandidates(const Candidates& candidates) {
53 for (const Candidate& candidate : candidates) {
54 RTCError error = VerifyCandidate(candidate);
55 if (!error.ok())
56 return error;
57 }
58 return RTCError::OK();
59}

61IceConfig::IceConfig() = default;
62
63IceConfig::IceConfig(int receiving_timeout_ms,
64 int backup_connection_ping_interval,
65 ContinualGatheringPolicy gathering_policy,
66 bool prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs,
67 int stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms,
68 bool presume_writable_when_fully_relayed,
69 int regather_on_failed_networks_interval_ms,
70 int receiving_switching_delay_ms)
71 : receiving_timeout(receiving_timeout_ms),
72 backup_connection_ping_interval(backup_connection_ping_interval),
73 continual_gathering_policy(gathering_policy),
74 prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs(
75 prioritize_most_likely_candidate_pairs),
76 stable_writable_connection_ping_interval(
77 stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_ms),
78 presume_writable_when_fully_relayed(presume_writable_when_fully_relayed),
79 regather_on_failed_networks_interval(
80 regather_on_failed_networks_interval_ms),
81 receiving_switching_delay(receiving_switching_delay_ms) {}
82
83IceConfig::~IceConfig() = default;
84
85int IceConfig::receiving_timeout_or_default() const {
86 return receiving_timeout.value_or(RECEIVING_TIMEOUT);
87}
88int IceConfig::backup_connection_ping_interval_or_default() const {
89 return backup_connection_ping_interval.value_or(
90 BACKUP_CONNECTION_PING_INTERVAL);
91}
92int IceConfig::stable_writable_connection_ping_interval_or_default() const {
93 return stable_writable_connection_ping_interval.value_or(
94 STRONG_AND_STABLE_WRITABLE_CONNECTION_PING_INTERVAL);
95}
96int IceConfig::regather_on_failed_networks_interval_or_default() const {
97 return regather_on_failed_networks_interval.value_or(
98 REGATHER_ON_FAILED_NETWORKS_INTERVAL);
99}
100int IceConfig::receiving_switching_delay_or_default() const {
101 return receiving_switching_delay.value_or(RECEIVING_SWITCHING_DELAY);
102}
103int IceConfig::ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity_or_default() const {
104 return ice_check_interval_strong_connectivity.value_or(STRONG_PING_INTERVAL);
105}
106int IceConfig::ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity_or_default() const {
107 return ice_check_interval_weak_connectivity.value_or(WEAK_PING_INTERVAL);
108}
109int IceConfig::ice_check_min_interval_or_default() const {
110 return ice_check_min_interval.value_or(-1);
111}
112int IceConfig::ice_unwritable_timeout_or_default() const {
113 return ice_unwritable_timeout.value_or(CONNECTION_WRITE_CONNECT_TIMEOUT);
114}
115int IceConfig::ice_unwritable_min_checks_or_default() const {
116 return ice_unwritable_min_checks.value_or(CONNECTION_WRITE_CONNECT_FAILURES);
117}
118int IceConfig::ice_inactive_timeout_or_default() const {
119 return ice_inactive_timeout.value_or(CONNECTION_WRITE_TIMEOUT);
120}
121int IceConfig::stun_keepalive_interval_or_default() const {
122 return stun_keepalive_interval.value_or(STUN_KEEPALIVE_INTERVAL);
123}
